716336f-a.text:
1941-1947 Amsterdam Avenue, a row of frame houses at and adjoining the N.E. corner of 156th Street. Also shown are 423-417 West 156th Street; 419 is a 2 1/2-story frame residence. The corner house, it will be noted, houses the J.J. McCormick.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 378.
